  "texts": [
    "Compared with the state-of-the-art black-box RAG methods, AAR and REFEED, the improvement in our approach is also significant.",
    "Moreover, from Table 1 we can see that our method consumes substantially fewer tokens than the other black-box RAG methods.",
    "On average, our approach reduces the number of input tokens per question by approximately half across the three datasets compared with REFEED and AAR.",
    "It demonstrates that our approach not only enhances Top-5 Top-10 Top-20 Top-50 50 60 70 80 90 100 Recall@K Contriever One Label (Has_Answer) One Label (LLM_Prefer) Bi-Label RAG performance but also improves computational efficiency by preventing the LLM from being overloaded with excessive irrelevant tokens.",
    "Effect of Bi-label Document ScorerIn this section, we experimentally investigate the impact of the bi-label document scorer on RAG performance."
